2 and on page 8, lines 34-39, by rewriting the lines to read:
3
4 ""Section 3.1. Regular Municipal Elections. Regular municipal elections shall be held in each
5 odd-numbered year in accordance with the uniform municipal election laws of North
6 Carolina.even-numbered year. Elections shall be conducted on a nonpartisan basis and the results
7 determined using the nonpartisan plurality method as provided in G.S. 163-292.partisan basis.
8 Except as otherwise provided, the primary and election shall be held and conducted in accordance
9 with the general laws governing primaries and elections for county officers. Notwithstanding
10 Article 11 of Chapter 163 of the General Statutes, the Union County Board of Elections may set
11 the date and time completed petitions must be timely submitted for verification."";
12
13
14
15 and on page 8, lines 41-42, by inserting between the lines:
16
17 "SECTION 5.(c) No municipal elections shall be conducted in the City of Monroe
18 in 2025. The terms of office for the Mayor and three Council Members in the City of Monroe
19 serving on the effective date of this section whose terms are set to expire in 2025 shall be
20 extended by one year. The terms of office for the three Council Members in the City of Monroe
21 serving on the effective date of this section whose terms are set to expire in 2027 shall be
22 extended by one year. Regular municipal elections in the City of Monroe shall resume in even-
23 numbered years beginning in 2026 with the same staggering of terms as when elections were
24 conducted in the odd-numbered years.
25 SECTION 5.(d) Subsection (a) of this section becomes effective at the time of the
26 organizational meeting held in accordance with G.S. 160A-68 in December 2026. In order to
27 implement subsection (a) of this section, the 2026 elections shall be conducted as if the provisions
28 of subsection (a) of this section were already in effect. Subsection (c) of this section is effective
29 when it becomes law and applies to elections held on or after that date.".
